inside the .env you put the database url 

.env is just a file that stores secret/config values 

for example 

DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://postgres:mypassword@localhost:5432/bar_ticket_api

.env file = the storage box
DATABASE_URL = the name of the value
postgresql+psycopg://... = the actual database URL

.env file
   ↓
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://...
   ↓
load_dotenv()
   ↓
os.getenv("DATABASE_URL")
   ↓
Python now has the database URL
   ↓
create_engine(DATABASE_URL)

